<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1325,284,1190]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,447,924,950]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Comments</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[463,688,924,949]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Scirtothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="akakia">
<emphasis box="[463,688,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Scirtothrips akakia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of one of the two species­groups within 
<taxonomicName box="[264,402,964,989]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Scirtothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[264,402,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Scirtothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that inhabit 
<taxonomicName box="[561,643,964,989]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[561,643,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Acacia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the other being the 
<taxonomicName box="[905,1111,964,989]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Scirtothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albomaculatus">
<emphasis box="[905,1111,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">S. albomaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group). Together with 
<taxonomicName box="[324,437,1004,1029]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Scirtothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kirrhos">
<emphasis box="[324,437,1004,1029]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">S. kirrhos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[453,582,1004,1029]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Scirtothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moneres">
<emphasis box="[453,582,1004,1029]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">S. moneres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[639,794,1004,1029]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Scirtothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriseta">
<emphasis box="[639,794,1004,1029]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">S. quadriseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species lacks definite sculpturing in the ocellar region, the first abdominal tergite lacks setae, and females exhibit obvious melanic coloration, which is especially dark on abdominal segments IX and X but with a dark area inside the ocellar triangle. The posteromarginal cilia on the forewing are straight, although a few 
<typeStatus box="[335,448,1164,1190]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">paratypes</typeStatus>
have 
<number box="[518,557,1164,1190]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1­2</number>
of these cilia very faintly wavy.
</paragraph>
